As a developer:-

      clone down the repository
        run npm i to install package.json.

      To run the mongodb in the terminal type
        mongod --dbpath db

      To start the server type
        node server.js

      To run the test you can run the test by typing in the terminal.

        mocha or gulp

    Open a new tab in the command line and run 'mongo', then 'use my_db'
    Send a POST request in another tab with: http POST :3000/api/user {'name': , 'active': , 'date': };
    Send a GET request with: http GET :3000/api/user/
    Send a PUT request with: http PUT :3000/api/user/ {'name': , 'active': , 'date': }
    Bonus: Send a GET request to list all users with with: http GET :3000/api/all
